NOTE FOR THE MAINTAINER:

This header identifies the project as AGPL-3.0-licensed. Before publishing,
replace this file's body with the FULL canonical AGPL-3.0 text from:

    https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.txt

(Keep the copyright line above at the top.) GitHub will then correctly detect
and display the license as "AGPL-3.0". The package.json "license" field is set
to "AGPL-3.0-only" to match.

Why AGPL-3.0 for Excogni: it keeps the project genuinely open and self-hostable
while requiring anyone who runs a MODIFIED version as a network service to make
their source available - which prevents a closed-source SaaS fork and protects
the open-core path, without restricting honest self-hosting or contribution.
